President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. These include David H. Stevens for Assistant Secretary for Housing and Federal Housing Commissioner at the Department of Housing and Urban Development, Harold Hongju Koh for Legal Adviser at the State Department, and Dr. Yvette Roubideaux for Director of Indian Health Service at the Department of Health and Human Services. Additionally, President Obama designated Judge Emily C. Hewitt to be the Chief Judge of the U.S. Court of Federal Claims. Each nominee brings a wealth of experience and expertise to their respective roles.